This article is a transcript of a press gaggle by Deputy Press Secretary Bill Burton aboard Air Force One en route to New York on July 16, 2009. Burton discusses President Obama's upcoming speech at the NAACP, the progress on health care reform, and other topics such as foreclosures and assistance for companies like CIT. He also addresses questions about the President's meetings with Republican senators and the possibility of a Senate vote on health care before the August recess.